<DOC><DOCNO> AP890827-0006 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-08-27-89 1152EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-TyphoonRoger     08-27 0173</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Typhoon Roger,0177</SECOND><HEAD>Two Dead, Two Missing as Tropical Storm Hits Western Japan</HEAD><DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A storm with 55 mph winds and heavy rains causedlandslides and flooding Sunday that left two people dead and threemissing, police said.   Seven people were reported injured by objects thrown by the winds.   The storm, earlier designated Typhoon Roger, had been downgradedto a tropical storm by the time it hit western Japan, forecasterssaid.   The heavy rains flooded 550 houses, caused about 70 landslidesand damaged or destroyed roads in 40 places, a police official said.   The storm hit Cape Muroto on Sunday morning and had moved northto Fukui in central Japan by early evening, forecasters said.   The police official said a 61-year-old man was buried by alandslide in Ome on the outskirts of Tokyo, and an 8-year-old girldrowned after falling into a swollen river in Saitama statenorthwest of Tokyo.   The official said three men were missing. Two of them fell intoflooded rivers, one while repairing a bridge.</TEXT></DOC>